article.headline: Penn State 78, Western Carolina 63
article.story: MILWAUKEE (AP) -- Danny Morrissey scored 16 points to lead Penn State to a 78-63 victory Monday over Western Carolina in the second round of the Black Coaches Association Classic. Marlon Smith added 14 points, Aaron Johnson 13, Ben Luber 11 and Geary Claxton 10 for the Nittany Lions. Johnson also had 24 rebounds. Penn State (1-1) won in the consolation bracket for teams that lost first-round games Sunday. Eight teams are in the tournament that ends Tuesday. David Berghoefer scored 19 and Kyle Greathouse hit five 3-pointers and had 17 points to lead Western Carolina (0-2). The Nittany Lions extended their eight-point halftime lead to 42-31 when Luber made a 3-pointer to open the second half. The Catamounts pulled within seven at 44-37 on a Greathouse 3-pointer, but the Nittany Lions scored six straight points, including four by Claxton, for a 51-37 advantage. Smith scored 11 points to lead Penn State to a 39-31 halftime lead.
